HAVANA , October 9 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Cuban anti-drug forces have seized nearly 100 kilograms of drugs and detained 40 drug dealers in Havana 's Jose Marti International Airport during the period from January to September .
The drugs , including cocaine , marijuana , hashish and heroin , were mostly bound for Europe , the `` Granma '' newspaper quoted authorities as saying , today .
The confiscations and detentions were attributed to the efforts and collaboration of the Cuban Customs and Interior Ministry .
Forty -one operations were carried out this year against international drug trafficking , 2.5 tons of drugs confiscated , and 63 foreigners and 10 Cubans detained .
About two tons of cocaine hidden in a motorboat flying a Honduran flag were seized in the Cuban waters early this month .
